content.description: Do the first couple moves of Storm Troopers to the slopers, get your feet off the block some how and follow the slopers right to a jug and top out.
content.protection: Some Pads.. 4 or so with a couple big ones.  The landing isn't perfect by any means and you could blow off holds and have a weird fall.
content.location: Just behind Pete's Pebble in what is now known as "The Baraboo Sex Pit".

content.description: Starting on a right hand undercling and your left hand on the block work your way out the roof on cool slopers to a finicky throw for the lip.
content.protection: A few pads.  Not tall, kinda rocky landing though.
content.location: Ten feet above the Pete's Pebble Boulder

content.description: With a good hold for the right and an edge for the left, set a heal and smack a sloper.  Continue onwards.
content.location: On Pete’s Pebble.  You will want the lake to be iced up for this.

climbs.name: Live With Porpoise
climbs.fa: Probably Ian CB and Ben Summay

content.description: Start with a sloper sidepull for the left, and a downpulling crispy hold for the right on the face.  Squeeze up the arete!
content.location: On Pete’s Pebble.  You will want ice on the lake for this one.

content.description: Start with right hand on a sloper, left on edge.  Gain a pinch (start hold for Another Coin in the Wishing Whale) and fire big left to the obvious jug.  Definitely possible to add a few moves from the right.  The lake must be frozen for this!
content.protection: A couple pads and a frozen lake.
content.location: On Pete’s Pebble boulder.  The one on the lake.

content.description: Start low on middle of boulder, bump out to crimp and rock up to slopey jug.  Top-out.
content.location: This boulder is approx. 10ft off the trail, about 50ft before Pete's Pebble.

content.description: Start on good jug, go up to good crimp and pinch and gun for jug.
content.location: Just off of the trail directly across from the diving rock, aka Pete's Pebble.

climbs.name: Another Coin in the Wishing Whale

content.description: Start matched on an obvious edge/pinch on the right side of the face.  Bust big left to the prominent jug and top out.  Starting from the jug is a V0/1 Walk the Plank.  A lower start from edges goes at V5.
content.location: On Pete’s Pebble.  You will want ice on the lake for this.

content.description: Right along the trail is the Diving Rock, Pete's Pebble.  Across from that is a nice V2, perhaps the best on the park.
